## AdaptiveTeamV2 Results
- V2a (aggressive crisis mode): 5.58 — WORSE, crisis mode too aggressive
- V2b (gentle late-game scaling): 8.82 — still worse than V1's 10.62
- Conclusion: V2 doesn't improve over V1. Stick with AdaptiveTeam.

## Economy Analysis (8a seed 1)
- Peak: 22 friendly junctions at step 1000 (economy ~200 each)
- Mid-game: 10-20j from step 2000-5000 (economy declining)
- Late game: 4j from step 7500+, carbon=0 permanently
- Score: dominated by early-mid game performance
- 5000 steps of late-game collapse costs ~6 points

## Key Insight: Economy crisis mode is counterproductive
- Dropping aligners when min_res=0 hurts more than it helps
- Carbon=0 is temporary (recovers in 100-200 steps)
- Each step without aligners reduces running average permanently
- Better to keep aligners and let idle-mine handle recovery

